    "reasoning": "To implement the 100-bit left/right rotator, we need to handle three main cases: loading new data, shifting left, and shifting right. We'll use a flip-flop to store the current state of the shift register. When the load signal is asserted, we'll update the shift register with the new data. When the shift left or right enable signals are asserted, we'll perform the respective rotation operation. For the shift left operation, we'll move each bit one position to the left and place the most significant bit (MSB) into the least significant bit (LSB). For the shift right operation, we'll move each bit one position to the right and place the least significant bit (LSB) into the most significant bit (MSB). All other cases, including when neither enable signal is asserted, will maintain the current state of the shift register.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n\tinput logic clk,\n\tinput logic load,\n\tinput logic [1:0] ena,\n\tinput logic [99:0] data,\n\toutput logic [99:0] q\n);\n\ntypedef enum logic[1:0] {\n\tLOAD,\n\tLEFT,\n\tRIGHT,\n\tNO_OP\n} control_t;\n\ncontrol_t control;\nalways_ff @(posedge clk or posedge load) begin\n\tif (load)\n\t\tcontrol <= LOAD;\n\telse if (ena == 2'b10)\n\t\tcontrol <= LEFT;\n\telse if (ena == 2'b01)\n\t\tcontrol <= RIGHT;\n\telse\n\t\tcontrol <= NO_OP;\nend\n\nlogic [99:0] shift_reg = 100'd0;\nalways_ff @(posedge clk) begin\n\tcase (control)\n\tLOAD:\n\t\tshift_reg <= data;\n\tLEFT:\n\t\tshift_reg <= {shift_reg[98:0], shift_reg[99]};\n\tRIGHT:\n\t\tshift_reg <= {shift_reg[1], shift_reg[99:1]};\n\tdefault:\n\t\t;\n\tendcase\nend\n\nassign q = shift_reg;\n\nendmodule"
